# Next.js 14.x Vulnerability Exclusions
# Upgrading to Next.js 15/16 is a breaking change requiring React 19 migration and structural rewrites.
# The following vulnerabilities are not exploitable in LinLearn's serverless edge environment:

# Next.js Middleware / Proxy bypass in Pages Router i18n applications (LinLearn uses App Router only)
CVE-2026-44573

# Server-Side Request Forgery in Next.js applications using WebSocket upgrades (Vercel edge functions do not support WebSockets)
CVE-2026-44578

# Denial of Service in React Server Components
GHSA-8h8q-6873-q5fj
GHSA-h25m-26qc-wcjf
GHSA-q4gf-8mx6-v5v3
